Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C. Chop the @baking potato{1} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Halve the @brioche hot dog buns{2} (but not all the way through) and set aside. Pop the wedges on a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{} and season with a @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Toss to coat, make sure they are in a single layer. Roast in on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking. When the wedges have about 5 mins left, pop the brioche rolls on the middle shelf on another baking tray for ~{5%minutes}.

Trim the @carrot{1} and coarsely grate (no need to peel). Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} then halve lengthways. Thinly slice widthways. Put them in a #large bowl{} and set aside. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on high heat. Once the pan is hot, add the @beef strips{240%g} along with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir-fry until browned on the outside, then remove from the pan, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The steak strips are cooked when they are no longer pink in the middle.

Add a drizzle of @oil{} to the now empty pan if it is dry and reduce the heat to medium. Add the shallot, stir-fry until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}, then add the steak back in along with the cheese and half the @soured cream{75%g}. Cook for ~{1%minute} to heat through, then remove from the heat. Add a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} and stir everything together.

Season the remaining soured cream with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}, add to the lettuce and carrot and mix together. Taste and add more salt and pepper if you feel it needs it.

Spoon the cheesy steak filling into each roll and serve with the wedges and slaw alongside. Enjoy!